Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Xenophon. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), 32, 23. From the same die as an example from Crocodilopolis illustrated in Senol 2016.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0960)
